The big question there is whether he knew that the material he leaked would be seen by al-Qaida members. The prosecution has presented evidence that Manning was trained not to put classified information online, that he knew the enemy in general used the Internet, and that Osama bin Laden had in his possession when he was killed digital copies of some of the documents that Wikileaks published.
